review_blob: Bright, bright orange color, big lasting head, cloudy. Nose citrusy, orange and lime, understated but pleasant. Flavor also "light", sweet, malty but extremely nice, honey and almonds and oranges and vanilla. Finish smooth, sweet, short.

Very artificial and strong taste of raspberry. The beer taste is hard to be found. The visual is nice, different...
If I could turn back time, wouldnt ask for this beer again.

Very good beer! I must admit, its the first abbey beer I ever tried, and I liked it very much.
Its a little sweetened and strong, oats taste is clear but soft.
This beer looks like a colored honey and its head goes away quickly.
The bootle is very very beautifull.

Very good strong bock. Very dark with browned head. Toasted cofee and a little bit of chocolate, sweet.

Last time i tried to mix it up with another beer (Devassa Tropical Lager) and.... SUPRISE!!!! it got even better!!!!!!!
 if you have the oportunity, try it.
Bottle of Caracu anf a bottle of Devassa Tropical Lager in a 1L glass. This misture was of the best "beer" i ever tried!!!!
Its not bad, but give me a strange feeling at the stomach. Another standart brazilian pilsener. Wattery thin yellow beer. Thin head that stays a long time in the glass, witch is good.

Very good beer for me. I cant really explain the taste, but its just like Paulaner, same taste, same good looking.
Gladely, its not seasonal anymore !!!!!!!!
Bad tastes and headaches after you drink it. Never seen no one that drinks it because he likes it. It only sells a bit because its very very cheap. Yellow color, no head, very watery.
Watery yellow colored beer. Light hope aroma. Its becoming to sell a lot in Brazil cause of the fact that its cheap and an average beer, just like most of the brazilians best sellers beers.

The look of this one is pretty standard stuff. Medium gold, white head. The aroma is typical lager, though not as watery as some in the same category.
Theres a strong metal taste and a light lemon taste. Its a fact, it tastes bad, but you can turn it into a different and not so bad beer if you put a peace of lemon into it. It worths to do it one time.

Well... I really dont like it. First time I tried I was expecting a great beer. "Uhhmmm Heiniken? It must be a good imported beer!" It was looking like a good beer but when it came to my mouth...arrhg Terrible. No tastes at all, strong bad beer taste in the water. White head that dissapears in 2 seconds. Strong bad beer aroma.
Strangely tastes just like the Erdinger hefe. More creamy and a little more sweet. The color is dark brown andvery nice. Little browned and very creamy head. It goes down nice, and refreshing.

I just love it! Not the best for me but... I love it!! Spice, soft wheat and bubblegum aromas. Hazy apricot, fair sized, rocky white head. Flavour has wheat, banana and some corriander.As hefe weizens go, its an adequate sample, and goes down nice, and refreshing.
Very yellow beer, small white head , good tastes. i really didnt like the green 35cl bottle. its a bit smooth. for me, a reguler good beer, nothing special, but good

Almost the same taste os the regular Skol, but more lighter, more wattery and more alcohol. Looks better in the bottle because of the very beautifull bottle that looks like a dancing woman body.  But instead of beeing a better beer than the regular Skol, its worse.

I must say, its really not a very good beer, its only... good. If you drink it one time you might just say: "average!". But... go on drinking it... go on... you will just say: "one of the best". I can tell you why. Because it makes you feel good, like youre free from your problems, you just drink it and beautifull nasty womens appears in front of you, the sun stars to shine and the food gets more tasty.
Its the best beer to get drunk. no headaches in the following mourning.
Not a good beer for me. Nice looking golden color, but the taste isnt good and i realy cant describe it very well. the finish tasting is light sweet.
Clear color, wattery beer. Used to be the best brazilian beer when the brand was more restricted. It began to sell a lot and the quality has decreased. Its still a good refreshing drink
The Pope used to drink this beer.and its my favoorite beer so far. The drinking sensation is like drinking a velvet stuff. Pope has more credit iwith me now.
